From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Codex <codex@example.com>
Date: Tue, 30 Jun 2026 16:05:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] deb: drop obsolete libpcre3 dependency

Kong 3.9.1 builds PCRE2 10.44 through Bazel and links it statically into the
OpenResty/nginx binary.  The repository's manifest checks also assert that
nginx does not depend on dynamic libpcre or libpcre2 runtime libraries.

The Debian package metadata still lists `libpcre3`, which is the old PCRE 1.x
runtime package name.  That package is unavailable in newer Debian environments
such as forky, and it is not required by this Kong build.

Remove the stale dependency instead of replacing it with a PCRE2 runtime
package.
---
 build/package/nfpm.yaml | 1 -
 1 file changed, 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/build/package/nfpm.yaml b/build/package/nfpm.yaml
index bdb01ec..18f25b0 100644
--- a/build/package/nfpm.yaml
+++ b/build/package/nfpm.yaml
@@ -70,7 +70,6 @@ overrides:
   deb:
     depends:
     - ca-certificates
-    - libpcre3
     - perl
     - libyaml-0-2
   rpm:
-- 
2.45.0
